&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for an enthuastic person to join our phlebotomy team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;to work across all ouh sites including John Radcliffe, Churchill and Horton General Hospital Banbury.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be flexible and have good skills dealing with patients.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We work on wards and in opd so you will not be working in one area.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It would be helpful if you have experience but we will train you to the&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;required standard.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need to be able to work 1 morning week day and Saturday and Sunday morning for this post.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It would be helpful if you hold a drivers licence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;14 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
